List of Gongen * {{ill|Akiba Gongen|ja|秋葉権現|12=draft}} ([[秋葉権現]]) * {{ill|Atago Gongen|ja|愛宕権現|12=draft}} ([[愛宕権現]]) *{{ill|Chimyō Gongen|ja|智明権現|12=draft}} ([[智明権現]]) *{{ill|Chōkai Shugendō|ja|鳥海修験|lt=Chōkai-san Daigongen|12=draft}} *{{ill|Futarasan Gongen|ja|二荒権現|12=draft}} ([[二荒権現]]) – Nikkō Shugendō ([[日光修験]]) *{{ill|Hachiōji Gongen|ja|八王子権現|12=draft}} ([[八王子権現]]) *{{ill|Haguro Gongen|ja|羽黒権現|12=draft}} ([[羽黒権現]]) – Haguro Shugendō ([[羽黒修験]]) * {{ill|Hakone Gongen|ja|箱根権現|12=draft}} ([[箱根権現]]) *{{ill|Hakusan Gongen|ja|白山権現|12=draft}} ([[白山権現]]) – Hakusan Shugendō ([[白山修験]]) * {{ill|Hikosan Gongen|ja|英彦山|lt=Hikosan Gongen|12=draft}} ([[英彦山|英彦山権現]]) * {{ill|Himuro Gongen|ja|氷室権現|12=draft}} * {{ill|Hirō Gongen|ja|飛瀧権現|12=draft}} ([[飛瀧権現]]) * {{ill|Sannō Gongen|ja|山王権現|lt=Hiyoshi Sannō Gongen|12=draft}} ([[山王権現|日吉山王権現]]) – {{ill|Sannō Shintō|ja|山王神道|12=draft}} ([[山王神道]]) * {{ill|Ishizuchi Daigongen|ja|石鎚大権現|12=draft}} ([[石鎚大権現]]) * {{ill|Isurugi Gongen|ja|石動権現|12=draft}} * {{ill|Izuna Gongen|ja|飯縄権現|1=Izuna Gongen|12=draft}} ([[飯縄権現]]), also called "Izuna Myōjin" and enshrined in Izuna Shrine in [[Nagano, Nagano|Nagano]], is similar to a [[tengu]] and represents the kami of [[Mount Iizuna]].<ref>Encyclopedia of Shinto, [http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=193 Izuna Gongen], accessed on October 6, 2008</ref> * {{nihongo|{{ill|Izusan Gongen|ja|伊豆山権現|12=draft}}|伊豆山権現}} or {{nihongo|Hashiri-yu Gongen|走湯権現}} is the spirit of a hot spring on Izusan, a hill in [[Shizuoka Prefecture]], enshrined in the [[Izusan Jinja]]<ref>Jaanus, ''Izusan Gongen'', accessed on October 6, 2008.</ref> *{{ill|Kasuga-no-Kami|ja|春日神|fr|Kasuga_no_Kami|lt=Kasuga Gongen|12=draft}} *{{ill|Kirishima Rokusha Gongen|ja|霧島六社権現|12=draft}} * {{ill|Konpira Gongen|ja|金毘羅権現|12=draft}} ([[金毘羅権現]]) * {{ill|Kumano Gongen|ja|熊野権現|12=draft}} ([[熊野権現]]), also known as {{nihongo|Three Mountains of Kumano|熊野三山}}.<ref name="kumano">Encyclopedia of Shinto, [http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=1076 Kumano Shinkō], accessed on October 6, 2008</ref><ref>[http://www.sekaiisan-wakayama.jp/english/s_sanzan.htm Kumano Sanzan] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080609225919/http://www.sekaiisan-wakayama.jp/english/s_sanzan.htm|date=2008-06-09}}, World Heritage Registration Association, accessed on October 13, 2008</ref> The kami enshrined in the three Kumano Sanzan Grand Shrines and worshipped in [[Kumano shrine]]s are the three Kumano mountains: Hongū, Shingū, and Nachi.<ref name="kumano" /> * {{ill|Nezu Gongen|ja|根津神社#歴史|lt=Nezu Gongen|12=draft}} ([[根津神社#歴史|根津権現]]) * {{ill|Ochi Daigongen|ja|越知大権現|1=Ochi Daigongen|12=draft}} ([[越知大権現]]) – Hakusan Shugendō ([[白山修験]]) * {{ill||Omatsu Daigongen|ja|お松大権現}} * {{ill|Sanki Daigongen|ja|三鬼大権現|12=draft}} ([[三鬼大権現]]) * {{nihongo|{{ill|Sannō Gongen|ja|山王権現|12=draft}}|山王権現}} or {{nihongo|Hie (alternatively ''Hiyoshi'') Sannō Daigongen|日吉山王大権現}} is a guardian deity worshiped in [[Tendai]] spread from [[Mount Hiei]]. It is treated as a Buddhist title of Shinto [[Oyamakui no Kami]]. * {{ill||Sekison Gongen|ja|石尊権現}} * {{ill|Seiryū Gongen|ja|清瀧権現|12=draft}} ([[清瀧権現]]) was enshrined in [[Jingo-ji]] in Takao as the tutelary kami of [[Shingon Buddhism]] by [[Kūkai]].<ref>Jaanus, ''Seiryū Gongen'', accessed on October 6, 2008</ref> * {{ill|Shiramine Daigongen|ja|白峯大権現|12=draft}} ([[白峯大権現]]) * {{ill|Suzuka Gongen|ja|片山神社 (亀山市)|lt=Suzuka Gongen|12=draft}} ([[片山神社 (亀山市)|鈴鹿権現]]) – {{ill|Shamanism|ja|巫覡|12=draft}} ([[巫覡]]) * {{ill|Tateyama Gongen|ja|立山権現|12=draft}} ([[立山権現]]) – Tateyama Shugendō ([[立山修験]]) *{{ill|Yuga Daigongen|ja|瑜伽大権現|12=draft}} ([[瑜伽大権現]]) * {{nihongo|{{ill|Zaō Gongen|ja|蔵王権現|12=draft}}|蔵王権現}} or {{nihongo|Kongō Zaō Bosatsu|金剛蔵王菩薩}} is a deity worshiped in [[Shugendō]].<ref>Encyclopedia of Shinto, [http://eos.kokugakuin.ac.jp/modules/xwords/entry.php?entryID=201 Zaō Gongen], accessed on October 6, 2008</ref>
