 three Kumano mountains: Hongū, Shingū, and Nachi.<ref name="kumano" /> * {{ill|Nezu Gongen|ja|根津神社#歴史|lt=Nezu Gongen|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nezu Gongen|qq=}} ([[:ja:根津神社#歴史|根津権現]]) * {{ill|Ochi Daigongen|ja|越知大権現|1=Ochi Daigongen|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ochi Daigongen|13=User:Immanuelle/Ochi Daigongen|qq=}} ([[:ja:越知大権現|越知大権現]]) – Hakusan Shugendō ([[:ja:白山修験|白山修験]]) * {{ill|Omatsu Daigongen|ja|お松大権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Omatsu Daigongen|qq=}} * {{ill|Sanki Daigongen|ja|三鬼大権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sanki Daigongen|qq=}} ([[:ja:三鬼大権現|三鬼大権現]]) * {{nihongo|{{ill|Sannō Gongen|ja|山王権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sannō Gongen|comment=enwiki is a redirect}}|山王権現}} or {{nihongo|Hie (alternatively ''Hiyoshi'') Sannō Daigongen|日吉山王大権現}} is a guardian deity worshiped in {{ill|Tendai|en|Tendai|WD=Q855964|lt=Tendai|1=Tendai}} spread from {{ill|Mount Hiei|en|Mount Hiei|WD=Q748040|lt=Mount Hiei|1=Mount Hiei}}. It is treated as a Buddhist title of Shinto {{ill|Oyamakui no Kami|en|Oyamakui no Kami|WD=Q10935105|lt=Oyamakui no Kami|1=Oyamakui no Kami}}. * {{ill|Sekison Gongen|ja|石尊権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sekison Gongen|qq=}} * {{ill|Seiryū Gongen|ja|清瀧権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Seiryū Gongen|qq=}} ([[:ja:清瀧権現|清瀧権現]]) was enshrined in {{ill|Jingo-ji|en|Jingo-ji|WD=Q1075034|lt=Jingo-ji|1=Jingo-ji}} in Takao as the tutelary kami of {{ill|Shingon Buddhism|en|Shingon Buddhism|WD=Q550182|lt=Shingon Buddhism|1=Shingon Buddhism}} by {{ill|Kūkai|en|Kūkai|WD=Q222227|lt=Kūkai|1=Kūkai}}.<ref>Jaanus, ''Seiryū Gongen'', accessed on October 6, 2008</ref> * {{ill|q|lt=Shiramine Daigongen|ja|白峯大権現|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiramine Daigongen|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 白峯寺|1=Shiromine-ji Temple|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11579651}} ([[:ja:白峯大権現|白峯大権現]]) * {{ill|Suzuka Gongen|ja|片山神社 (亀山市)|lt=Suzuka Gongen|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suzuka Gongen|1=Katayama Shrine (Kameyama)|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q43594929}} ([[:ja:片